<br>
==Annotations==
'''''Goim nachez'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Yiddish'') ''Gentiles' pleasure.'' The usual spelling today is: ''Goyim naches''. The expression is pejorative, implying that while Gentiles may derive pleasure from an event, such pleasure is beneath a Jew.

