==Annotations==
'''''Morituri te salutant'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''They who are about to die salute thee.''<ref>Gifford (1988) 475-476.<br>Thornton (1968) 378.</ref> It is commonly said that these words were the [[w:Ave Imperator, morituri te salutant|traditional formula]] used by [[w:Gladiator|gladiators]] when saluting the [[w:Emperor of Rome|Emperor]] at the start of the gladiatorial games. In fact they were spoken by ''[[w:Naumachia|naumacharii]]'' before a mock naval encounter which took place on [[w:Lake Fucino|Lake Fucino]] in 52 CE in the presence of the [[w:Claudius|Emperor Claudius]].<ref>[http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/L/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Claudius*.html Suetonius, ''Life of Claudius'' 21:6.]</ref>


