[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=597]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''— cum —'''''{{spaces|5}}''[[wikt:cum|Cum]]'' is a Latin preposition meaning ''with''. In English it is used as a combining form to indicate a dual nature or function. Here, the narrator (Bloom?) is alluding to the dual purpose for which Murphy went outside: to relieve himself (libation) and to have a drink of liquor (potation).

