<br>
==Annotations==
'''''genus omne'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''all that kind''.<ref>Gifford (1988) 562.</ref> The usual form of this phrase is: ''[[wikt:et hoc genus omne|et hoc genus omne]]'' (''and all this sort of thing''). The narrator (Bloom?) is using the Latin phrase as a simple substantive, as though it were a synonym for ''[[wikt:ilk|ilk]]''. This unusual practice is typical of his affected style in this episode.

